node.html: Teaching Materials for Python Programming and Basic Web Application Development.

Web application that allows users to search for jobs based on their skills. This project was built while applying Agile methodologies (Scrum) as part of IS212: Software Project Management in Singapore Management University. Learn more about this project here

Machine Learning project on Emotional Speech Detection using the RAVDESS dataset. This project was built using packages like - ipykernel, librosa, pandas, matplotlib, seaborn, resampy, and tensorflow.
Internet of Things (IoT) application that monitors noise levels. This application was built using Grafana, Nginx, Docker, and Python.
Website for the SUSS Virtual Lab Infrastructure team. This website was built using HTML and CSS and is hosted on GitHub Pages.
Simple website on bullying and cyberbullying. This website was used to teach secondary school students about coding and cyberbullying, as part of a volunteery project.

Digital Skills Matching Platform that connect job seekers with training programs and job opportunities. Bit By Bit aims help to promote digital empowerment and bridge the skills gap in Singapore's labor market. This project is a submission for the Build for Good Hackathon.
Natural disaster relief mobile application using containerization and microservice architecture. SafeMe aims to provide real-time updates on individuals dealing with disasters.
PropertyPlanners simplifies the resale flat buying process by offering a user-friendly platform with essential features like summary statistics, charts, and regional maps.

Beginner Game Development project built using C# and Unity. This project was built to learn the basics of game development and to learn how to use Unity. The end project is a 2D Platformer based on the anime, Naruto.

Insuretech website that serves as an open platform for agents to connect with customers. By utilising AI to provide intelligent recommendations to customers, Syndesi puts forward an agent-centric platform that builds connects and improve customer experience.

frontmatter.title: Computational Search for Viral Species Jump

node.html: Solo major project with ASTAR that aims to predict the next viral species jump.
Smartphone application that uses image classification to help guide the visually impaired cross the road safely. This project is a submission for the Code For Good Hackathon.
